{"questionId":"22267528","questionHtml":"<p>Solve the differential equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></math>, given that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Give your answer in the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>recognition that an integrating factor is required&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>∫</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mi>y</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mi>x</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to integrate right hand side using integration by parts&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>∫</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup></math></p>\n<p>substitute initial values <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>into an integrated expression involving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>⇒</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22267528","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ1.7","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Solve the differential equation dydx=x+y, given that y=2 when x=0. Give your answer in the form y=fx.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"7","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.10—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.18—1st order DE’s – Euler method, variables separable, integrating factor, homogeneous DE using sub y=vx"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}